  "text": "Some groups published larger series of biopsies of other nerves including the superficial peroneal nerve as fragments from the adjacent peroneus brevis muscle may be taken during the same surgical procedure (see below: vascular changes). The superficial radial nerve may be chosen when symptoms predominate in the upper limbs. Obturator nerve biopsy is considered to be quite useful to differentiate motor neuropathies and lower motor neuron diseases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
